From 2021 we launched our OBC Reader application. Its inclusion on this Privacy Policy won't change anything previously mentioned above, all the Policies remain the same for OnlineBookClub.org
Your account could also be accessed and / or created (by you, the user) from our application OBC Reader. All the information sent by the application to our server will be secure using an HTTPS connection, and will be held to all the policies stated above.
Also, as stated above, in our mobile application, only â€œyour user nameâ€, â€œyour passwordâ€ and â€œyour emailâ€ will be required to create and enter your account. Any other personal information will be optional. Your date of birth will be required only to determine your access to books classified as 18+.
Your account will not be deleted simply because you stop using it. If you want to delete it, you can do it through an option given to you on the website or from your account settings on the OBC Reader application.
If you request to delete your account we will delete your personal information. This action is irrevocable. Because OnlineBookClub.org is not only a great space to share information about books between book lovers, but it is also a company that actually pays its reviewers, we need to comply with other business policies that require us to keep some information, but it will never be shared with anyone. Regarding your reviews, posts, and any other shared content, if you did share them you agreed to grant OnlineBookClub.org a nonexclusive, royalty-free, perpetual, irrevocable, and fully sublicensable right to use, reproduce, modify, adapt, publish, perform, translate, create derivative works from, distribute, and display such content throughout the world in any media. Therefore, none of this content will be deleted, nor the user name associated with it.
We will always be at your service if you have any doubt about this privacy policy at: development@onlinebookclub.org
OnlineBookClub.org was created over 15 years ago and has over 5 million members. It is a FREE site for readers.
Data Protection Policy: We comply with all United States data-protection laws. We will not share your email address or other sensitive data.
